        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In my project those classes are instantiated with an additional parameter and in the currect version of ZF there's no way to do that.\r\nBy moving the creation of the class into a method, it will be possible to override the instantiation in child classes of Zend_Db_Table_Abstract.\r\n\r\nThis is a trivial and no behavior or public API-changing change.\r\n\r\nI've attached the patch to this issue.\r\nSorry if I should've done something incorrectly, this is my first submission to ZF. :)\r\n\r\nEDIT:\r\nOh, and it would be awesome, if this patch came in the next minor release of ZF, as we'll use this in one of our projects. :)"
